####################Individual Captures Plots########################
###########################IndiCa V0.4###############################
####Function to create visualization of individual capture histories
##using the KBMN data.

####The final product is a *.svg file. Use your webbrowser (e.g. Google
##Chrome, Mozilla Firefox) to open the file. You can only drag and drop
##the file on the browser to open it.

####Make sure that the working directory (R function "getwd()") is the
##same where the codes are placed (e.g. (...)/IndiCa/codes). If not,
##change it using "setwd()" function.

#####Function IndiCa
######Arguments:
####spp: Define the species. Use the four letter code. Multispecies
########still not available
####site: Define the site. Use the four letter code. Multisite still
########not available
####age: Define age class. AHY, HY or All. All is used by default.
########Note: If you select an age (AHY or HY), the individuals that
########were captuptured with both age classes will not show.
########To be updated!


########Version notes:
########By now, individuals that were captured in more than one place
########and/or with more than one species code are excluded from the
########database.


source("IndiCa.R")

IndiCa(spp="YWAR",site="WOOD",age="AHY")
